@Patrick J. There absolutely are puzzles where the rebus across and down are different. One typically separates the across part from the down part with a slash (/).

In such cases though, there is typically some theme or connection that relates the two as in kit/kat or in a puzzle where the rebuses had a playing card value in one direction and a playing card suit in the other.

You could fill this puzzle *technically* correctly with bidirectional rebuses (square 1 would be “A/BLA” for example), but if done that way there would be no clever connection between the across and down part of the rebus, making it an improper (or at least unclever)  use of that mechanism.

